  <Subject Subject_ID="300025821">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300025254</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>people in crafts and trades by activity [300025254], people in crafts and trades [300025253], people by occupation [300024980], people (agents) [300024979], People (hierarchy name) [300024978], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those engaged in making changes to an object or structure so that it will closely approximate its state at a specific time in its history. When changes made are to prevent further deterioration, see "preservationists." More generally, for those who undertake treatment, preventive care, and research directed toward long-term safekeeping of cultural and natural heritage, see "conservators."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050615/IFLA Glossary for Art Librarians (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aquellos que se dedican a realizar cambios a objetos o estructuras logrando que se asemejen lo más posible a su momento de creación en la historia.  Cuando los cambios realizados son para prevenir el deterioro, ver preservación. Más adecuado para quienes se encargan de los tratamientos, cuidados preventivos, además de la investigación a largo plazo para el cuidado de los depósitos que albergan el patrimonio cultural y natural, ver "conservadores.”</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zij die veranderingen in een object of structuur aanbrengen om de staat daarvan op een bepaald tijdstip in het verleden zo dicht mogelijk te benaderen. Gebruik 'milieu- en natuurbeschermers' wanneer de veranderingen gericht zijn op de voorkoming van verdere achteruitgang. Gebruik meer in het algemeen 'restauratoren' voor hen die behandeling, preventieve zorg en onderzoek uitvoeren gericht op het behoud van culturele en natuurlijke erfgoederen op lange termijn.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>修整物件或結構，使其回復至與過去特定時段之狀態相仿的人員。 修整物件或結構以防止其進一步毀壞者，以「預防性保存人員」稱之。負責文化及自然遺產之處理、維護及長期保存並進行相關研究的人員，則泛稱為「維護專家」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aqueles empenhados em fazer alterações em um objeto ou estrutura de modo que se aproxime muito de seu estado em um momento específico de sua história. Quando as alterações feitas forem para evitar maior deterioração, consulte "preservacionistas". De forma mais geral, para aqueles que realizam tratamento, cuidados preventivos e pesquisas direcionadas à proteção de longo prazo do patrimônio cultural e natural, consulte "conservadores". </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
